data.title: Forbes: Akshay Kumar is only Indian star included in list of highest grossers
data.meta_description: Recently, Forbes magazine has released its list of highest-grossing celebrities. Kylie Jenner has topped it. Akshay Kumar has become the onl... | News Track
data.text:
Recently, Forbes magazine has released its list of highest-grossing celebrities. Kylie Jenner has topped it. Akshay Kumar has become the only Bollywood star to make a place in this list. Apart from Akshay, Priyanka Chopra's husband Nick Jonas has also made a place in this list. Kim Kardashian's half-sister Kylie Jenner has topped the list.

Veteran Filmmaker Anil Suri lost his life due to Corona

She has earned $ 590 million in the last 12 months, which makes her number 1 on this list and makes her the highest grossing celeb. Kylie's brother-in-law and Kim Kardashian's husband Kanye West are at number two apart from her. His earnings are $ 170 million. While Kim herself is at number 48 in this list. Famous tennis player Roger Federer is at number three in the Forbes 2020 list. The famous footballer Cristiano Ronaldo is at number four in Forbes' list. In this list, American talk show host and comedian Ellen Degeneres is at number 12 in the Forbes 2020 list. His year-round earnings have been $ 84 million.

In this list, Priyanka Chopra's husband Nick Jonas and his brother Joe and Kevin's Jonas Brothers are at number 20 with 68.5 million dollars. Talking about the only Indian star Akshay Kumar, he is at number 52 in this list with 48.5 million dollars.
